cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR. 

This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically reading comprehension, and proposes a method for unsupervised domain adaptation. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes deep neural networks, which suggests it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of BERT contextual representation and adversarial learning techniques could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), respectively. Finally, the paper deals with text classification and transfer learning, which could also fit under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
